      • changeOrientationX

        public static int changeOrientationX(int startPos,
                                     int x,
                                     int y)
        Flips the x coordinate given for the green and red zones according to which corner the robot is starting in. This is done to make the search algorithm identical for all four starting corners.
        Parameters:
        startPos - the corner in which we are starting in
        x - the x coordinate being passed in by WiFi
        y - the y coordinate being passed in by WiFi
        Returns:
        the x portion of the flipped coordinate

      • changeOrientationY

        public static int changeOrientationY(int startPos,
                                     int x,
                                     int y)
        Flips the y coordinate given for the green and red zones according to which corner the robot is starting in. This is done to make the search algorithm identical for all four starting corners.
        Parameters:
        startPos - the corner in which we are starting in
        x - the x coordinate being passed in by WiFi
        y - the y coordinate being passed in by WiFi
        Returns:
        the y portion of the flipped coordinate
